13:30.247 --> 13:32.716
So, what exactly did you mean
by "disturbing"?

13:32.810 --> 13:35.010
- What?
- You said my dream was disturbing.

13:35.012 --> 13:36.841
That's a pretty strong word.

13:37.214 --> 13:38.947
Well, you're messing around
with another man.

13:38.949 --> 13:40.749
You don't think I should be
disturbed by that?

13:40.751 --> 13:41.617
It's a dream.

13:41.619 --> 13:42.618
Haven't you ever had a dream

13:42.620 --> 13:44.049
about a celebrity before...

13:44.051 --> 13:46.822
Phoebe Cates or Lindsay Wagner
or somebody?

13:46.824 --> 13:48.257
I don't have dreams.

13:48.259 --> 13:49.658
I'm not talking about in life.

13:49.660 --> 13:51.093
I'm talking about when you're asleep.

13:51.095 --> 13:53.262
So am I... I go to sleep, it's dark,

13:53.264 --> 13:55.064
I wake up, put on my shoes, and go.

13:55.066 --> 13:57.800
What? That can't be true.
Everybody dreams.

13:57.802 --> 14:00.769
Not me. Dreaming is just showing
off while you're asleep.

14:00.771 --> 14:03.072
Look, it was nothing.
You know how dreams are.

14:03.074 --> 14:05.841
Well, apparently you don't,
but most people do.

14:05.843 --> 14:08.010
Anyway, it started out
with me in the bathroom

14:08.012 --> 14:09.211
and the gorilla in the next stall

14:09.213 --> 14:10.512
was handing me toilet paper.

14:10.514 --> 14:12.881
And then, all of a sudden,
I'm backstage at The Sands

14:12.883 --> 14:15.284
with Frank and we're having
a shrimp cocktail.

14:15.286 --> 14:16.752
And then the stage manager knocked

14:16.754 --> 14:18.520
and said it was time to go on,
and Frank said,

14:18.522 --> 14:20.189
"Tell Sammy to do five more minutes."

14:20.191 --> 14:22.191
And then he asked me how my day was,

14:22.193 --> 14:23.827
and I told him, and we made out.

14:24.760 --> 14:27.634
Frank Sinatra, the original Danny Ocean,

14:28.032 --> 14:29.665
asked you about your day?

14:29.667 --> 14:32.501
Yeah. Maybe he was interested in me.

14:32.503 --> 14:34.236
That's just dumb.

14:36.873 --> 14:39.842
Oh, I can't believe we're gonna
blow our one chance in life

14:39.844 --> 14:41.510
to beat the Donahues.

14:41.512 --> 14:43.812
They're not the Down-ahues,
they're the Perfect-hues.

14:43.814 --> 14:45.914
They're good at everything,
unlike some people

14:45.916 --> 14:48.650
who just pretend they're good
at stuff when they're not.

14:49.987 --> 14:51.687
Ah! God, it's bright.

14:51.689 --> 14:52.955
Ahh! Geez, come on.

14:55.191 --> 14:57.593
The key! It's got to be for the door!

14:57.595 --> 14:58.760
How are we supposed to get this?

14:58.762 --> 14:59.995
Oh, look. Look at the letters.

14:59.997 --> 15:01.630
I think we got to make words
with the switches.

15:01.632 --> 15:04.066
Okay, Sue, get in there.
It's your time to shine.

15:04.068 --> 15:06.635
Yeah, shine away, you little star, you.

15:08.172 --> 15:11.807
Listen, Milt, I just want you to know

15:11.809 --> 15:14.209
I get it that sometimes
you might need an escape.

15:14.211 --> 15:16.311
You know, I myself am a writer.

15:16.313 --> 15:17.579
So far it's only been a sentence,

15:17.581 --> 15:18.881
but it's been very well received.

15:18.883 --> 15:20.411
Oh, yeah? Well, what is it?

15:21.152 --> 15:23.507
Really? You'd like to hear it?

15:23.888 --> 15:25.619
Wow. Okay.

15:26.123 --> 15:28.490
I always keep it with me
in case I want to noodle on it.

15:30.628 --> 15:34.062
"As his eyes fluttered open,

15:34.064 --> 15:37.599
the boy saw the sun
had already gently nudged awake

15:37.601 --> 15:40.502
its captives,
yesterday's mistakes vanished

15:40.504 --> 15:43.071
to wispy nothings,
and the father he thought

15:43.073 --> 15:45.684
long dead was standing at his door."

15:46.343 --> 15:47.595
Hey, that's great.

15:48.279 --> 15:49.311
Really?!

15:49.313 --> 15:51.113
D-Do you have any notes or advise?

15:51.115 --> 15:52.948
No, no, no. I wouldn't change a word.

15:52.950 --> 15:54.950
Mom, Mom! What do you got?

15:54.952 --> 15:57.386
David S. Rosenthal loves my sentence!

15:57.388 --> 15:59.421
It's inspired me to finish my novel.

15:59.423 --> 16:02.491
Which pose do you like for the
book jacket... this or this?

16:02.493 --> 16:03.926
Not now, Brick. Time's running out.

16:03.928 --> 16:05.314
Sue needs quiet.

16:05.996 --> 16:07.796
Okay, okay... Five-letter word...

16:07.798 --> 16:09.464
Uh..."Chair"! "Chair"!

16:10.367 --> 16:11.767
Uh, "Table"! No, "Zombies"!

16:11.769 --> 16:13.035
That's not even five letters.

16:13.037 --> 16:14.970
Look, what about that list
of patients we found?

16:14.972 --> 16:17.372
Dr. I.N. Sane's first patient was Clara.

16:17.374 --> 16:19.841
Try that. No, there were
100 names on that list.

16:19.843 --> 16:21.643
Just let Sue do this.
She's our best chance.

16:21.645 --> 16:23.045
You got this, Sue. Oh, my God!

16:23.047 --> 16:24.546
I'm telling you, try "Clara."

16:24.548 --> 16:26.048
Axl, shush. I don't want to hear it.

16:26.050 --> 16:27.049
No one's getting out of here

16:27.051 --> 16:28.283
if you don't let me work those levels!

16:28.285 --> 16:29.651
Your family sure does fight a lot.

16:29.653 --> 16:30.786
Oh, "Orson"!

16:30.788 --> 16:32.354
Well, at least when we get
the door open,

16:32.356 --> 16:34.156
you get to leave.

16:34.158 --> 16:35.507
I'm stuck with them.

16:35.509 --> 16:37.092
I'm telling you, she's not gonna get it.

16:37.094 --> 16:38.860
Axl, what is the matter with you?

16:38.862 --> 16:40.329
Why do you always
have to bring her down?

16:40.331 --> 16:41.563
This is the one thing she's good at.

16:41.565 --> 16:42.664
Can't she just have that?

16:42.666 --> 16:44.633
Oh, is she... Is she good at this?

16:44.635 --> 16:46.668
Axl, I'm not gonna
say it again... shut it.

16:46.670 --> 16:48.904
Sue's our best shot at this.
Come on, Sue. Take us home.

16:48.906 --> 16:52.574
Um... Belle! N... Ariel. Pocahontas!

16:52.576 --> 16:54.643
She's just naming Disney Princesses!

16:54.645 --> 16:56.378
That's it! I can't hold it anymore.

16:56.380 --> 16:57.579
It's for the good of the family.

16:57.581 --> 16:59.214
Sue's a big, fat cheater.

16:59.216 --> 17:01.049
That's right. She's cheated
at every game she's ever played.

17:01.051 --> 17:02.551
She palms marbles. She stacks decks.

17:02.553 --> 17:03.552
You ever played "Sorry!" with her?

17:03.554 --> 17:05.454
Well, sorry, you got screwed.

17:05.455 --> 17:07.122
Sue, is that true?

17:08.324 --> 17:10.157
He's right!

17:10.327 --> 17:11.893
I don't know what I'm doing.

17:11.895 --> 17:13.428
We are gonna lose to the Donahues,

17:13.430 --> 17:15.430
and it is all my fault.

17:15.432 --> 17:18.200
I am a cheater.

17:18.202 --> 17:21.036
But that ends today.

17:21.038 --> 17:23.238
I am not gonna let my past define me.

17:23.240 --> 17:27.342
I am moving forward
with confidence, with honor.

17:27.344 --> 17:30.912
Starting now, Sue Heck wins for real!

17:32.583 --> 17:34.316
Time has expired.

17:34.318 --> 17:36.551
The zombie apocalypse has begun.

17:36.553 --> 17:38.387
Mankind is doomed.

17:38.389 --> 17:40.322
Please exit through the fail door.

17:40.324 --> 17:42.557
No!

17:42.559 --> 17:45.594
No! We're not entering 2017
through the fail door.

17:45.596 --> 17:48.063
We have done it every year,
and I am sick of it.

17:48.065 --> 17:50.068
Mom, just admit it... we suck.

17:50.070 --> 17:52.301
No, if anybody sucks, it's Rowdy.

17:52.303 --> 17:53.802
We asked for a clue,
and she didn't get back to us

17:53.804 --> 17:55.670
- for at least two minutes.
- Yeah.

17:55.672 --> 17:57.272
- That's true.
- That's not fair.

17:57.907 --> 17:59.456
Hey, Rowdy,

17:59.458 --> 18:01.009
we want our two minutes.

18:01.011 --> 18:02.577
I'm meeting my cousin for dinner.

18:02.579 --> 18:05.180
Look, I may not care about much,

18:05.182 --> 18:07.749
I barely care about this,
but I know what's right,

18:07.751 --> 18:09.318
and so do you, Rowdy!

18:09.320 --> 18:11.720
You know you owe us two minutes.

18:11.722 --> 18:13.121
Fine.

18:15.025 --> 18:16.625
Okay, let's do this.

18:16.627 --> 18:17.965
Axl, you're up. Yep.

18:18.762 --> 18:22.030
C-L-A-R-A.

18:22.032 --> 18:24.499
Ah-ah-ah-ahh!

18:26.102 --> 18:27.936
Yes, we got it, we got it, we got it.

18:27.938 --> 18:28.937
Whoo.

18:28.939 --> 18:30.572
Suck it, Donahu...

18:30.840 --> 18:32.974
No!

18:32.976 --> 18:35.177
Why does 2017 have it out for us?

18:35.179 --> 18:37.346
Why won't this stupid door open?

18:37.348 --> 18:38.513
Come on, open!

18:38.515 --> 18:40.449
W-W-Wait. You see that?

18:41.150 --> 18:44.686
O-P-E-N.

18:44.688 --> 18:46.588
Oh, my God!

18:46.590 --> 18:49.424
We did it, Hecks... and Milt!

18:49.426 --> 18:51.193
Whoo! And check it out!

18:51.195 --> 18:52.294
We beat the Donahues!

18:54.398 --> 18:56.098
I don't know who these Donahues are,

18:56.100 --> 18:57.599
but we kicked their butts!

18:57.601 --> 19:00.435
- Yeah, we did!
- Okay, everybody, hands in!

19:00.437 --> 19:01.636
What's the book?

19:01.638 --> 19:02.571
"The Catcher in the Rye"!

19:02.573 --> 19:04.206
Okay, one, two, three.

19:04.208 --> 19:06.074
"The Catcher in the Rye"!

19:09.278 --> 19:10.412
Yes!

19:10.414 --> 19:11.713
Give me a high five!

19:11.715 --> 19:13.415
Give me another one!

19:18.640 --> 19:20.308
So, how was your day?

19:20.310 --> 19:21.409
What do you mean, how was my day?

19:21.411 --> 19:23.010
You were there. We beat the Donahues.

19:23.012 --> 19:24.712
It was awesome.
Yeah, well, I don't know.

19:24.714 --> 19:27.014
You're dreaming about guys
asking you about your day,

19:27.016 --> 19:29.083
and I know we've been
pretty busy lately,

19:29.085 --> 19:30.851
and I don't always ask, so I thought,

19:31.747 --> 19:33.154
you know, maybe I should.

19:33.156 --> 19:35.656
Oh. Well, it was good.

19:35.658 --> 19:37.124
Thanks.

19:42.732 --> 19:44.532
Let's see what you dream about tonight.

19:50.105 --> 19:52.039
Well, Milt, it's an honor that someone

19:52.041 --> 19:54.842
of your esteemed profession
likes what I do.

19:54.844 --> 19:57.211
I will carry your approval
with me always.

19:58.280 --> 20:00.514
Okay, then. See you around.

20:12.861 --> 20:14.295
Look around.

20:14.297 --> 20:15.796
No zombies anywhere!

20:15.798 --> 20:17.798
You're welcome, mankind.

20:17.800 --> 20:21.168
Oh, my God. Winning without
cheating feels amazing.

20:21.170 --> 20:22.803
It is so much better.

20:22.805 --> 20:25.172
And I finally have a certificate
for my wall

20:25.174 --> 20:26.707
that doesn't say "Participant."

20:26.709 --> 20:27.842
Yeah!

20:29.245 --> 20:31.612
Everyone has a different kind of escape.

20:31.614 --> 20:33.881
Sometimes we escape into a good book,

20:33.883 --> 20:36.083
sometimes we escape into our dreams.

20:36.085 --> 20:37.952
But one thing you can't escape from

20:37.954 --> 20:40.788
is the Hecks after a rare victory.

20:43.191 --> 20:44.692
Oh, hey, Nancy.

20:44.694 --> 20:46.460
Just got back from the escape room...

20:46.462 --> 20:48.796
Made it out with 1:21 to spare.

20:48.798 --> 20:50.364
What was your time again?

20:50.366 --> 20:52.066
1:08.

20:52.068 --> 20:55.102
Oh, hey, Sean, turns out
when I looked in the mirror,

20:55.104 --> 20:57.405
all I saw was a guy who kicked your ass.

20:57.407 --> 20:58.706
Yeah, I don't know, Ron.

20:58.708 --> 21:00.041
If this mojo keeps up,

21:00.043 --> 21:01.075
I wouldn't get too attached

21:01.077 --> 21:02.343
to that giant spatula.

21:02.345 --> 21:04.578
Yep. Says right here
on the certificate...

21:04.580 --> 21:06.147
The Hecks won.

21:06.149 --> 21:08.849
No apostrophe necessary, Dotty.

21:09.885 --> 21:12.486
Well, that's impressive, you guys.

21:12.488 --> 21:14.722
I guess you're just better
at this than we are.

21:14.724 --> 21:16.891
You know, that's what's great
about you Donahues...

21:16.893 --> 21:18.626
You have fun no matter what.

21:18.628 --> 21:21.095
Happy New Year.

